BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp
 -content/uploads/2026/06/Red-White-Bloom-V2.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 6/Red-White-Bloom-V2.jpg
UID:U4KquRgcp0f5YULDyqcCh
SUMMARY:Red\, White & Bloom
DTSTAMP:20260629T025250Z
DTSTART:20260704T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the Fourth of July surrounded by beautiful blooms\, f
	estive fun\, and one of Houston’s most beloved fireworks displays! Join us
	 for “Red\, White & Bloom” on Saturday\, July 4\, from 8 – 11 p.m. in the 
	McGovern Centennial Gardens for a fantastic summer evening. \nThis year is
	 extra special as we mark America’s 250th birthday with a celebration pack
	ed with birthday party vibes! Enjoy free treats\, family-friendly activiti
	es\, music\, lawn games\, and more before the night wraps up with a specta
	cular view of the fireworks show from Miller Outdoor Theatre. \nBest of al
	l\, Red\, White & Bloom is FREE and open to the public! \nBring a blanket\
	, gather your friends and family\, and stroll through the vibrant garden s
	paces before settling in for the show. Spend Independence Day in this icon
	ic spot\, under the stars—a perfect setting for summer memories! \nThe fir
	eworks show at Miller Outdoor Theatre is set to start at approximately 9:4
	5 p.m. The complimentary food items are while supplies last. Additional fo
	od vendors will be offering items for purchase by Miller Outdoor Theatre.\
	n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/event/red-white-bloom/\n\nFrom Hermann Park Con
	servancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/red-white-bloom/
LOCATION:McGovern Centennial Gardens\, 1500 Hermann Drive\, Houston\, TX\, 
	77004\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp
 -content/uploads/2026/06/Red-White-Cruise-2026.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 6/Red-White-Cruise-2026.jpg
UID:gaxiEQG5rNXseOCgEa4CQ
SUMMARY:Red\, White & Cruise
DTSTAMP:20260629T025250Z
DTSTART:20260704T203000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Red\, White & Cruise where you can watch Miller Out
	door Theatre’s fireworks show light up the sky from the peaceful waters of
	 Hermann Park\, with a special pedal boat rental from 8:30–10:30 p.m. on S
	aturday\, July 4! \nAs we celebrate 250 years of American independence\, g
	ather your crew and watch the sky come alive with fireworks while cruising
	 across the lake in your own pedal boat under the stars. \nSaturday\, July
	 4\n8:30 – 10:30 p.m.  \n🎟️ $150 per boat (up to 4 people) includes:\n🕘 Boa
	t rental up to 2 hours\n🍿 Drinks & snacks\n🎊 Festive accessories\n🅿️ Reserv
	ed parking in Lot I near Lake Plaza\n⛵ Board anytime between 8:30–9:30 p.m
	. and enjoy the show from the water (fireworks begin at approximately 9:45
	 p.m.\, boats must return once fireworks finish) \nBOOK YOUR BOAT HERE!  \
	n🚨 Important Info: \n\nOne rider per boat must be 18+\nAll riders 18+ must
	 sign a digital waiver before boarding\nAt least one rider must be 18+\, w
	ith a physical government ID\, and sign a waiver before boarding\nTickets 
	are non-refundable\nEvent is rain or shine per Miller Outdoor Theatre’s pl
	an\nIn the event of lightning\, pedal boats will close\, and refunds will 
	be issued \n\nThe purchase of a ticket includes an up-to 2-hour pedal boat
	 ride for up to 4 people to enjoy the sight of Miller Outdoor Theatre’s fi
	reworks show\, drinks\, snacks\, festive treats\, and a reserved parking s
	pot in Lot I near Lott Hall by Lake Plaza (starting at 8 p.m.). Only one t
	icket purchase of $150 is needed for a 4-person boat (i.e. it is the cost 
	per boat\, not per rider).  \nA reminder that at least one rider per boat 
	must be 18 years or older.  All riders 18 years or older must sign a digit
	al waiver before boarding. Tickets are non-refundable. We are following Mi
	ller Outdoor Theatre’s plan for their event and fireworks show which is ra
	in or shine. If there is lightning in the area\, we will close the pedal b
	oats and ticket holders will receive a refund.  \nPlease arrive early to a
	llow time to park in Lot I as roads in the Park will be closed by HPD and 
	closures are subject to change based on their purview.  \n\nhttps://herman
	npark.org/event/red-white-cruise-2/\n\nFrom Hermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/red-white-cruise-2/
LOCATION:Lake Plaza
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
